This paper is about generative models for face image synthesis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of objective functions and competitions between generators and discriminators, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper focuses on generating photo-realistic images, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the preservation of facial identity, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) research.
